      "author": "Emberleif",
      "description": "Chronoboard 0.7.0 focuses on onboarding, documentation, and workflow clarity.\r\n\r\n### Highlights\r\n- Added a managed getting started guide inside the vault:\r\n  - `Getting Started With Chronoboard`\r\n- Added a managed changelog note inside the vault:\r\n  - `Chronoboard - Changelog`\r\n- New users now get the guide opened automatically on first install\r\n- Updating users now get the changelog opened automatically once per version\r\n- Added command palette actions for opening the guide and changelog\r\n- Added a compact `?` help icon in the task panel\r\n- Added clearer setup guidance around required status frontmatter\r\n- Improved totals header presentation and sort control behavior\r\n- Improved time entry note handling so renamed notes still reopen correctly through aliases and entry IDs\r\n- Added template support for time entry notes with Chronoboard fields appended after template frontmatter\r\n\r\n### Clarified interactions\r\n- Double click a time block to remove it\r\n- Hold and drag a time block to move it\r\n- Use `Ctrl+Z` or `Cmd+Z` to undo adding or removing a time block\r\n- Removing a task from the left rail does not remove existing tracked time from the board\r\n\r\n### Setup note\r\nChronoboard reads tasks from a configured folder and expects them to use your configured frontmatter property, `Status` by default, unless they are explicitly included through `Always include tasks`.",
